comments.content: Mitochondrial fatty acid β-oxidation (FAO) is crucial in the prodcution of energy, especially during fasting and metabolic stress. Fatty acids (FAs) are oxidized through 4 reaction mechanisms, and this pathway describes the mitochondrial beta-oxidation of dietary long chain fatty acids.
